  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DRC COVID-19 Global Appeal West Africa Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DRC is present in &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.drc.ngo/where-we-work/west-africa&quot;&gt;6 countries&lt;/a&gt; in the West Africa Region and has implemented Covid-19 specific activities in all of these countries: &lt;i&gt; Burkina Faso, Central African Republic &amp; Niger &lt;/i&gt;.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In &lt;b&gt;Cameroon&lt;/b&gt;, DRC targeted rural communities with limited access to health care and reliable information, as well as people working in the informal sector. In &lt;b&gt; Mali &lt;/b&gt;, protection services were primarily dedicated to the internally displaced (IDPs) and conflict- and displacement- affected hosting communities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;b&gt; The OECD DAC CRS Purpose Codes &lt;/b&gt; used to describe this activity refer to the amount of people reached, seen as a percentage of all single instances of beneficiaries reached. This means that it can include double counting if single individuals have been counted multiple times for different sectors. 
&lt;i&gt;We have also referred to our reprogramming of funds related to our COVID-19 response in our current and recently closed IATI activities &lt;/i&gt;.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Targets for the Global Appeal for the region have been reached and exceeded in the sectors of: Protection, Economic Recovery and Basic Needs.</narrative>
  </description>
